Extension: Cross-version Extension `R5.EvidenceVariable.characteristic` for use in FHIR R4

0.0.1-snapshot-3
Official URL: http://hl7.org/fhir/5.0/StructureDefinition/extension-EvidenceVariable.characteristic Version:
Standards status: Trial-use Active as of 2026-02-06 Maturity Level: 0 Computable Name: ExtensionEvidenceVariable_Characteristic

This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element EvidenceVariable.characteristic for use in FHIR R4.

Context of Use

    This extension may be used on the following element(s)

    • Element ID: Extension.extension

    This extension is allowed for use with FHIR versions R4 to R4 .

Usage info

Usages:

  • This Extension is not used by any profiles in this Implementation Guide

You can also check for usages in the FHIR IG Statistics

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element EvidenceVariable.characteristic for use in FHIR R4.

  • linkId: id: Label used for when a characteristic refers to another characteristic.
  • description: markdown: A short, natural language description of the characteristic that could be used to communicate the criteria to an end-user.
  • note: Annotation: A human-readable string to clarify or explain concepts about the characteristic.
  • exclude: boolean: When true, this characteristic is an exclusion criterion. In other words, not matching this characteristic definition is equivalent to meeting this criterion.
  • definitionReference: Reference: Defines the characteristic using a Reference.
  • definitionCanonical: canonical: Defines the characteristic using Canonical.
  • definitionCodeableConcept: CodeableConcept: Defines the characteristic using CodeableConcept.
  • definitionExpression: Expression: Defines the characteristic using Expression.
  • definitionId: id: Defines the characteristic using id.
  • type: CodeableConcept: Used to express the type of characteristic.
  • method: CodeableConcept: Method for how the characteristic value was determined.
  • device: Reference: Device used for determining characteristic.
  • value: CodeableConcept, boolean, Quantity, Range, Reference, id: Defines the characteristic when paired with characteristic.type.
  • offset: CodeableConcept: Defines the reference point for comparison when valueQuantity or valueRange is not compared to zero.
  • code: code: Used to specify if two or more characteristics are combined with OR or AND.
  • threshold: positiveInt: Provides the value of "n" when "at-least" or "at-most" codes are used.
  • characteristic: base64Binary, boolean, canonical, code, date, dateTime, decimal, id, instant, integer, markdown, oid, positiveInt, string, time, unsignedInt, uri, url, uuid, Address, Age, Annotation, Attachment, CodeableConcept, Coding, ContactPoint, Count, Distance, Duration, HumanName, Identifier, Money, Period, Quantity, Range, Ratio, Reference, SampledData, Signature, Timing, ContactDetail, Contributor, DataRequirement, Expression, ParameterDefinition, RelatedArtifact, TriggerDefinition, UsageContext, Dosage, Meta: A defining factor of the characteristic.
  • instances: Quantity, Range: Number of occurrences meeting the characteristic.
  • duration: Quantity, Range: Length of time in which the characteristic is met.
  • description: markdown: Human readable description.
  • note: Annotation: A human-readable string to clarify or explain concepts about the timeFromEvent.
  • event: CodeableConcept, Reference, dateTime, id: The event used as a base point (reference point) in time.
  • quantity: Quantity: Used to express the observation at a defined amount of time before or after the event.
  • range: Range: Used to express the observation within a period before and/or after the event.

Maturity: 0

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element EvidenceVariable.characteristic for use in FHIR R4.

  • linkId: id: Label used for when a characteristic refers to another characteristic.
  • description: markdown: A short, natural language description of the characteristic that could be used to communicate the criteria to an end-user.
  • note: Annotation: A human-readable string to clarify or explain concepts about the characteristic.
  • exclude: boolean: When true, this characteristic is an exclusion criterion. In other words, not matching this characteristic definition is equivalent to meeting this criterion.
  • definitionReference: Reference: Defines the characteristic using a Reference.
  • definitionCanonical: canonical: Defines the characteristic using Canonical.
  • definitionCodeableConcept: CodeableConcept: Defines the characteristic using CodeableConcept.
  • definitionExpression: Expression: Defines the characteristic using Expression.
  • definitionId: id: Defines the characteristic using id.
  • type: CodeableConcept: Used to express the type of characteristic.
  • method: CodeableConcept: Method for how the characteristic value was determined.
  • device: Reference: Device used for determining characteristic.
  • value: CodeableConcept, boolean, Quantity, Range, Reference, id: Defines the characteristic when paired with characteristic.type.
  • offset: CodeableConcept: Defines the reference point for comparison when valueQuantity or valueRange is not compared to zero.
  • code: code: Used to specify if two or more characteristics are combined with OR or AND.
  • threshold: positiveInt: Provides the value of "n" when "at-least" or "at-most" codes are used.
  • characteristic: base64Binary, boolean, canonical, code, date, dateTime, decimal, id, instant, integer, markdown, oid, positiveInt, string, time, unsignedInt, uri, url, uuid, Address, Age, Annotation, Attachment, CodeableConcept, Coding, ContactPoint, Count, Distance, Duration, HumanName, Identifier, Money, Period, Quantity, Range, Ratio, Reference, SampledData, Signature, Timing, ContactDetail, Contributor, DataRequirement, Expression, ParameterDefinition, RelatedArtifact, TriggerDefinition, UsageContext, Dosage, Meta: A defining factor of the characteristic.
  • instances: Quantity, Range: Number of occurrences meeting the characteristic.
  • duration: Quantity, Range: Length of time in which the characteristic is met.
  • description: markdown: Human readable description.
  • note: Annotation: A human-readable string to clarify or explain concepts about the timeFromEvent.
  • event: CodeableConcept, Reference, dateTime, id: The event used as a base point (reference point) in time.
  • quantity: Quantity: Used to express the observation at a defined amount of time before or after the event.
  • range: Range: Used to express the observation within a period before and/or after the event.

Maturity: 0
